{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC25","role":"sampleCode","title":"Get ahead with quantum-secure cryptography"},"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to protect your app’s sensitive user data from the emerging threat of quantum computing, and safeguard user privacy. We’ll explore different quantum attacks, their impact on existing cryptographic protocols, and how to defend against them using quantum-secure cryptography. You’ll learn how to use quantum-secure TLS to secure network data, and use CryptoKit’s quantum-secure APIs for securing application data.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-314-Get-ahead-with-quantumsecure-cryptography"},"kind":"article","sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (20 min)","isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/314"}},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-314-get-ahead-with-quantumsecure-cryptography"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Key-Takeaways","text":"Key Takeaways","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"🔐 Passive quantum attacks are already relevant","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"⚡ Sensitive data needs quantum-secure encryption immediately"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"🛡️ iOS 26 provides automatic defence mechanisms"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"🆕 New CryptoKit APIs: Post-quantum HPKE (X-Wing), ML-KEM, ML-DSA","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Understanding-Quantum-Attacks","text":"Understanding Quantum Attacks","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Quantum attacks compromise the security of fundamental cryptographic mechanisms, including encryption and signatures."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Types:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Passive - does not require a quantum computer at the time of attack"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Active - requires the attacker to have access to a quantum computer"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Passive-Attack-Harvest-now-decrypt-later","text":"Passive Attack - Harvest now, decrypt later","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-314-HNDL-Attack","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Affects encryption"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Breaks confidentiality"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Since this is a ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"passive attack","type":"text"}]},{"text":", it is already relevant today.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Important","style":"important","type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"How it works:","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Attacker harvests encrypted data by observing the network"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Attacker waits until sufficiently powerful quantum computers become available","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Attacker decrypts harvested data using quantum computers","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Active-Attack","text":"Active Attack","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-314-Active-Attack"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Affects signatures"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Breaks authenticity"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Since we don’t have sufficiently powerful quantum computers yet, this is a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"future threat"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"How it works:"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Attacker intercepts a signature by observing network traffic"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Attacker steals the signing key from the signature using a quantum computer","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Attacker uses the stolen key to impersonate the user"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Quantum-secure-cryptography","text":"Quantum-secure cryptography","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"New quantum-secure cryptographic algorithms can be adopted today on traditional (non-quantum) devices."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Public-key-cryptography","text":"Public-key cryptography","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-314-Public-Key-Cryptography"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Current algorithms are based on computationally-intensive mathematical problems, which can be solved by quantum computers. ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Solutions:"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For encryption: Post-quantum Hybrid Public Key Encryption (HPKE)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Fore signatures: Post-quantum Hybrid Signatures","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both of the aforementioned solutions use a hybrid approach, integrating post-quantum and traditional algorithms. Attacking them demands breaking both layers."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Symmetric-key-cryptography","text":"Symmetric-key cryptography","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While these algorithms also rely on complex computational problems, quantum computers reduce their security only by a small constant factor."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Solution:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Double the key size"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Upgrade 128-bit ciphers to 256-bit"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Protecting-network-data","text":"Protecting network data","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Protecting against Harvest Now, Decrypt Later attacks is the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"top priority","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" now. To do so, quantum-secure encryption should be applied for data in transit."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple is already using quantum-secure encryption in iMessage since iOS 17.4","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside"},{"level":3,"anchor":"TLS-13","text":"TLS 1.3","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Includes a quantum-safe encryption enhancement, using a secure key exchange resistant to quantum attacks","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Most providers already support it","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Client-side-quantum-secure-TLS","text":"Client-side quantum-secure TLS","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Starting from iOS 26, quantum-secure encryption in TLS is enabled by default for:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"URLSession","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Network.framework"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is recommended to migrate away from legacy APIs like Secure Transport, as they won’t support quantum-secure TLS"}]}],"name":"Important","style":"important","type":"aside"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Server-side-quantum-secure-TLS","text":"Server-side quantum-secure TLS","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Quantum-secure TLS should also be enabled on the server side."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Most content\/website hosting providers already support and enable it by default","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For your own servers, you need to upgrade TLS explicitly","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS 26 introduces support for quantum-secure TLS across various built-in services such as ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CloudKit, Apple Push Notifications, iCloud Private Relay, Safari, Weather, Maps"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":", and other built-in apps","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Protecting-custom-protocols","text":"Protecting custom protocols","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In most cases, quantum-secure TLS provides sufficient protection against Harvest Now, Decrypt Later attacks. However, direct usages of cryptographic APIs in your app also require upgrading to their quantum-secure counterparts using "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"new CryptoKit APIs","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Quantum-secure-encryption-with-CryptoKit","text":"Quantum-secure encryption with CryptoKit","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Based on ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Post-quantum HPKE"}]}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Uses ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"X-Wing Key Encapsulation Mechanism (KEM)","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Uses "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"ML-KEM","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" as its post-quantum building block"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Large encryption size overhead"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Comparable or even better performance in comparison to traditional methods"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Hardware-isolated execution via Secure Enclave","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Formally verified","type":"text"}]}]}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Sample Post-quantum HPKE usage:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let ciphersuite = HPKE.Ciphersuite.XWingMLKEM768X25519_SHA256_AES_GCM_256","","\/\/ Recipient","let privateKey = try XWingMLKEM768X25519.PrivateKey.generate()","let publicKey = privateKey.publicKey","","\/\/ Sender","var sender = try HPKE.Sender(recipientKey: publicKey, ciphersuite: ciphersuite, info: info)","let encapsulatedKey = sender.encapsulatedKey","","\/\/ Recipient","var recipient = try HPKE.Recipient(privateKey: privateKey, ciphersuite: ciphersuite, info: info, encapsulatedKey: encapsulatedKey) ","","\/\/ Sender encrypts data","let ciphertext = try sender.seal(userData, authenticating: metadata)","","\/\/ Recipient decrypts message","let decryptedData = try recipient.open(ciphertext, authenticating: metadata)","#expect(userData == decryptedData)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While  post-quantum HPKE provides a simplified abstraction, CryptoKit gives developers the option to use "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"lower-level APIs","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" as well."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Quantum-secure-signatures-with-CryptoKit","text":"Quantum-secure signatures with CryptoKit","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Post-quantum hybrid signatures can be made using "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"ML-DSA","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Also offers hardware-isolated execution via Secure Enclave"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"columns":[{"size":1,"content":[]},{"size":1,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-314-Post-Quantum-CryptoKit"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"size":1,"content":[]}],"numberOfColumns":3,"type":"row"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"CryptoKit’s adherence to standard protocols means it can interoperate with any compliant server library, but Apple’s preferred choice is ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift Crypto","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Migration-checklist","text":"Migration checklist","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"checked":false,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Enable quantum-secure TLS on your servers","type":"text"}]}]},{"checked":false,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use URLSession or Network.framework for networking","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"checked":false,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Update server configuration to support quantum-secure TLS"}]}]},{"checked":false,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Replace custom encryption with Post-quantum HPKE"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Written-By","text":"Written By","type":"heading"},{"columns":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"terlan98","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":1},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Tarlan Ismayilsoy","level":3,"anchor":"Tarlan-Ismayilsoy"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/terlan98","overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributed Notes","type":"text"}],"isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/terlan98","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}],"size":4}],"numberOfColumns":5,"type":"row"},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Missing anything? Corrections? "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Legal Notice","type":"text"}]}],"type":"small"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All content copyright © 2012 – 2025 Apple Inc. All rights reserved.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Swift, the Swift logo, Swift Playgrounds, Xcode, Instruments, Cocoa Touch, Touch ID, FaceID, iPhone, iPad, Safari, Apple Vision, Apple Watch, App Store, iPadOS, watchOS, visionOS, tvOS, Mac, and macOS are trademarks of Apple Inc., registered in the U.S. and other countries.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This website is not made by, affiliated with, nor endorsed by Apple.","type":"text"}],"type":"small"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"references":{"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributions are welcome!","type":"text"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","title":"Contributions are welcome!"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25":{"kind":"article","title":"WWDC25","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 26, Swift 6.2, iOS\/macOS\/tvOS\/visionOS 26."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Foundation Models"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmKit"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PermissionKit"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25","role":"collectionGroup","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC25.jpg","type":"card"}]},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"},"WWDC25-314-Public-Key-Cryptography":{"identifier":"WWDC25-314-Public-Key-Cryptography","type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-314-Public-Key-Cryptography.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null},"terlan98.jpeg":{"identifier":"terlan98.jpeg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/terlan98.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"https://github.com/terlan98":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/terlan98","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GitHub"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/terlan98","title":"GitHub"},"WWDC25-314-Active-Attack":{"identifier":"WWDC25-314-Active-Attack","type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-314-Active-Attack.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/terlan98":{"images":[{"identifier":"terlan98.jpeg","type":"card"},{"identifier":"terlan98.jpeg","type":"icon"}],"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"iOS Developer","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"Tarlan Ismayilsoy (2 notes)","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/terlan98","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/terlan98"},"terlan98":{"identifier":"terlan98","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/terlan98.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":"Profile image of Tarlan Ismayilsoy","type":"image"},"WWDC25-314-HNDL-Attack":{"alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-314-HNDL-Attack.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC25-314-HNDL-Attack"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/314":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/314","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/314","checksum":null,"type":"download"},"https://":{"identifier":"https:\/\/","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Blog"}],"url":"https:\/\/","type":"link","title":"Blog"},"WWDC25-Icon.png":{"identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null},"WWDC25-314-Post-Quantum-CryptoKit":{"alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-314-Post-Quantum-CryptoKit.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC25-314-Post-Quantum-CryptoKit"},"WWDC25.jpg":{"identif